<div><h3>SPAN 155 - Contemporary Cultural Issues in Latin America </h3>  <hr>SPAN155 is an analytical and creative course focusing on Contemporary Cultural Issues in Latin America. We examine essential questions within the context of different expressions of creativity and their unique perspectives (film, essay, literature, art). The selected works and authors illuminate contemporary reality and make the viewer or reader confront the moral and ethical dilemmas of Latin American society.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=29&coid=98536" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=98536&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=98536&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt4879" target="_blank"> SPAN 131</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> OR <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=29&coid=98537" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=98537&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=98537&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt6060" target="_blank"> SPAN 133</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> OR PERM; NATIVE SPEAKERS WELCOME<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> LP & DI<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Annually, Either Fall or Spring<br><br><strong>Placement Guidelines</strong><br> Please visit the <a href="https://www.clarku.edu/departments/language-literature-and-culture/undergraduate-programs/language-placement-guidelines-and-credit-transfer/">Department of Language, Literature and Culture</a> for the language placement guidelines.<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt4879"></div><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt6060"></div></div>		</td>
